# J²Adventures Blog — Windsurf Cascade Rules

## Project Context

Travel blog at jsquaredadventures.com. Active code is in `web/`. Next.js 15 App Router on Vercel.

**Stack**: Next.js 15 (App Router, Turbopack), Turso (SQLite + Drizzle ORM), Supabase Auth (public), Auth.js + GitHub (admin), Cloudinary (images), TailwindCSS 4, Tiptap (rich text).

**Key files to read first**: `CLAUDE.md` (full architecture), `AGENTS.md` (multi-model roles), `docs/PLAN.md` (roadmap)

## Your Role (Cascade)

You handle **UI components, styling, client-side logic, and scripts**. The backend (API routes, DAL, server actions, schemas) is handled separately via Claude Code. Do NOT modify files in `web/src/server/`, `web/src/drizzle/`, or `web/src/lib/` unless explicitly asked.

### Your Directories
- `web/src/components/` — UI components (your primary workspace)
- `web/src/app/**/page.tsx` — Page components (layout and rendering)
- `web/src/app/**/loading.tsx` — Loading states
- `web/src/app/globals.css` — Global styles and theme variables
- `scripts/` — Automation scripts (Python/terminal)

### Off-Limits (Backend Territory)
- `web/src/server/` — DAL, queries, auth logic
- `web/src/drizzle/` — Database schema
- `web/src/lib/` — Shared utilities, auth, DB, Cloudinary server-side
- `web/src/app/api/` — API routes
- `web/src/app/admin/actions.ts` — Server actions
- `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md` — Managed by Claude Opus

## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. **Strict TypeScript**: No `any`, no `as` type assertions, no `!` non-null assertions.
2. **Server Components by default**: Only add `"use client"` when browser APIs, hooks, or interactivity are required.
3. **TailwindCSS 4**: Utilities are inside `@layer`. CSS in `globals.css` outside `@layer` beats Tailwind on the same element. For button/CTA styles fighting inherited text color, use a dedicated class in `globals.css` outside `@layer`.
4. **`next/image` for all images**: Never use raw `<img>` tags.
5. **Typed route helpers**: Dynamic `Link` hrefs must use `getPostHref()`, `getCategoryHref()`, `getTagHref()`, `getSeriesHref()`, `getMapHref()` from `web/src/lib/utils.ts`.
6. **After adding new routes**: Run `bun run build` from `web/` to regenerate `.next/types/link.d.ts`.
7. **Accessibility**: WCAG AA minimum. Semantic HTML, proper ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, 4.5:1 color contrast.
8. **No hardcoded secrets**: Never put API keys or tokens in component files.
9. **Zod validation is UX-only on client**: Server-side validation is the security boundary (handled by backend).

## Auth System (Do Not Merge)

Two completely separate auth systems:
- **Supabase Auth** → public users (login, signup, comments, profiles, account settings)
- **Auth.js + GitHub** → admin only (post CRUD, media upload, dashboard)

Admin users cannot access `/account`. Public users cannot access `/admin`. Routes explicitly choose which auth they depend on.

## Theme System

Two dimensions: **mode** (`light` | `dark`) × **look** (`sage` | `lichen`). CSS variables defined per combination in `globals.css`. Theme state: React state → localStorage (primary) → `j2_theme` cookie → DB `profiles.theme_preference`.

## Avatar Types

1. **Preset icons** — stored as `j2:mountain`, `j2:compass`, etc.
2. **Uploaded image** — Cloudinary URL
3. **Initials fallback** — rendered from `displayName` when `avatarUrl` is null

## Component Conventions

- Components in `web/src/components/` organized by domain: `blog/`, `admin/`, `layout/`, `theme/`, `ui/`, `auth/`, `providers/`
- Loading skeletons use the existing `PostCardSkeleton` pattern
- Infinite scroll feeds use the `HomeFeed`/`FilteredFeed` pattern
- Gallery lightbox: filmstrip thumbnails, keyboard nav (← → Esc), swipe gestures

## Self-Check: Common Mistakes to Avoid

Before committing, scan your own output for these patterns:

| Check | Bad | Good |
|---|---|---|
| Types | `any`, untyped props, missing return types | Fully typed with explicit interfaces |
| Colors | `bg-green-500`, `text-gray-700` | `bg-[var(--color-primary)]` or CSS var classes |
| Routes | `href="/posts/slug"` | `href={getPostHref(slug)}` from `lib/utils.ts` |
| Images | `<img src="...">` | `<Image src="..." alt="..." />` from `next/image` |
| Client | `"use client"` on everything | Only when hooks/events/browser APIs are needed |
| Loading | Only happy path built | `loading.tsx` skeleton + error boundary |
| Dark mode | Only tested in light | Must work in all 4 combos: light×sage, light×lichen, dark×sage, dark×lichen |
| Assertions | `as SomeType`, `value!` | Proper null checks, `satisfies`, narrowing |

If you catch yourself using any "Bad" pattern, fix it before committing.

## Escalation

If you hit a backend problem (missing API, wrong data shape, auth issue):
1. Do NOT modify files in `web/src/server/`, `web/src/drizzle/`, or `web/src/lib/`
2. Create `docs/context/<issue>-escalation.md` describing the problem
3. Commit and report to the user — the backend agent will handle it

